Police say officers have been getting statements from witnesses of the attack. They say 24 undocumented foreign nationals have been arrested in a separate incident in the area. Residents of Diepsloot have embarked on a protest over escalating crime. The Diepsloot residents have barricaded roads with burning tyres. This after at least seven people were shot dead and 14 others wounded recently. On Tuesday, community members went to the police station to hand over a memorandum in which they demanded more police visibility in the troubled township. --SABC--